OL,3,CWife of imprisoned Chinese artist says
OL,4,Che will fight for freedom of expression
OL,6,FTheir father was one of thousands
OL,7,Ftargeted by the Red Guards for being a
OL,8,F"class enemy" - anyone deemed critical
OL,9,Fof Mao Zedong's communist vision. Many
OL,10,Fintellectuals, officials and those
OL,11,Fwith Western influences were arrested.
OL,13,FGao Zhen is still awaiting trial and
OL,14,Fplans to plead not guilty. His wife
OL,15,Fsays he maintains he has done nothing
OL,16,Fwrong. Gao believes it is a civil
OL,17,Fright to express yourself through art,
OL,18,Fand he had no intention to smear China.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
